    {
      "id": "9f69666f_6f805b74",
      "file_path": "csit/plans/cps/setup.sh",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 123,
      "message": "NB: This is fine but we can mount a node as part of a test (worked on it a little as part of an old story). I've added the robot test for reference if you prefer this method.\n\n...\n\n*** Settings ***\nDocumentation         Mount Node PNFDemo2\n\nLibrary               Collections\nLibrary               OperatingSystem\nLibrary               RequestsLibrary\nLibrary               BuiltIn\n\nSuite Setup           Create Session     SDNC_URL    http://${SDNC_HOST}:${SDNC_PORT}\n\n*** Variables ***\n\n${auth}                 Basic YWRtaW46S3A4Yko0U1hzek0wV1hsaGFrM2VIbGNzZTJnQXc4NHZhb0dHbUp2VXkyVQ==\n${sdncBasePath}         /restconf/config\n\n*** Test Cases ***\n\nmount node\n    ${uri}=              Set Variable       ${sdncBasePath}/network-topology:network-topology/topology/topology-netconf/node/PNFDemo1\n    ${headers}=          Create Dictionary  Content-Type=application/json   Authorization=${auth}\n    ${jsonData}=         Get Binary File    ${DATADIR}${/}mountPNFDemo1.json\n    ${response}=         PUT On Session     SDNC_URL   ${uri}   headers=${headers}   data=${jsonData}\n    Should Be Equal As Strings              ${response.status_code}   201\n...",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7743,
